                        <h1>Mercedes Benz van oils</h1>
                        <p xmlns="">Mercedes Benz light duty commercial vehicles can benefit from high performance Mobil Delvac&trade; synthetic oils that have been formulated to meet MB-Approval 229.31, 229.51 and 229.52 specifications. For all Mercedes Benz light duty commercial vehicles there is a comprehensive range of Mobil Delvac&trade; oils you can trust.</p>

                        <p xmlns="">
                            <strong>Mercedes Benz 229.31, 229.51 and 229.52 approved oils</strong>
                            <br>

                            <a title="" target="" onclick="trackClick(this);" href="http://www.mobil.co.uk/UK-English-LCW/vanengineoils_mobil-delvac-city-logistics-m-5w-30.aspx" class="">Mobil Delvac&trade; City Logistics M 5W-30 </a>is a low ash synthetic engine oil, with MB-Approval 229.31, 229.51 and 229.52 manufacturer approval that provides long engine life and excellent engine protection against sludge &amp; wear.</p>

                        <p xmlns="">
                            <a title="" target="" onclick="trackClick(this);" href="http://www.mobil.co.uk/UK-English-LCW/vanengineoils_mobil-delvac-city-logistics-m-5w-30.aspx" class="">Mobil Delvac&trade; City Logistics M 5W-30 </a>provide excellent lubrication of diesel and gasoline engines operating in severe driving conditions typically encountered in city operations. These products are recommended by ExxonMobil for European engines for use in a wide range of light-duty commercial vehicles including those offered by Mercedes Benz.</p>

                        <p xmlns="">
                            <strong>Mercedes Benz 229.1 approved oils</strong>
                        </p>

                        <p xmlns="">
                            <a title="" target="" onclick="trackClick(this);" href="http://www.mobil.co.uk/UK-English-LCW/vanengineoils_mobil-delvac-light-commercial-vehicle-e-10w-40.aspx" class="">Mobil Delvac&trade; Light Commercial Vehicle E 10W-40</a> is a semi-synthetic engine oil, with MB 229.1 manufacturer approval, that supports long engine life and provides excellent engine protection against sludge &amp; wear.</p>

                        <p xmlns="">
                            <a title="" target="" onclick="trackClick(this);" href="http://www.mobil.co.uk/UK-English-LCW/vanengineoils_mobil-delvac-light-commercial-vehicle-e-10w-40.aspx" class="">Mobil Delvac&trade; Light Commercial Vehicle E 10W-40</a> provides excellent lubrication of diesel and gasoline engines operating in severe driving conditions such as those typically encountered in city operations. This product is recommended by ExxonMobil for European engines used in a wide range of traditional light-duty commercial vehicles.</p>

                        <p xmlns="">
                            <strong>How can you save money by using Mobil Delvac&trade;?</strong>
                        </p>

                        <p xmlns="">Fully and semi-synthetic oils such as Mobil Delvac&trade; circulate around Mercedes Benz engines more easily than traditional mineral oils, so engines operate more efficiently. Mobil Delvac&trade; also gets to work faster so your engine reaches peak operating efficiency quicker. These benefits mean your fleet of light duty vehicles could get more miles per gallon (mpg), saving you money on diesel, while also helping reduce the costs associated with engine maintenance and repair.</p>

                        <p xmlns="">
                            <br>

                            <strong>How does Mobil Delvac&trade; support my Mercedes Benz engines?</strong>
                        </p>

                        <p xmlns="">ExxonMobil recommends <a title="" target="" onclick="trackClick(this);" href="http://www.mobil.co.uk/UK-English-LCW/vanengineoils_mobil-delvac-city-logistics-m-5w-30.aspx" class="">Mobil Delvac&trade; City Logistics M 5W-30 </a>and <a title="" target="" onclick="trackClick(this);" href="http://www.mobil.co.uk/UK-English-LCW/vanengineoils_mobil-delvac-light-commercial-vehicle-e-10w-40.aspx" class="">Mobil Delvac&trade; Light Commercial Vehicle E 10W-40 </a>for normal to occasionally severe driving conditions, including city driving.</p>

                        <p xmlns="">
                            <a title="" target="" onclick="trackClick(this);" href="http://www.mobil.co.uk/UK-English-LCW/vanengineoils_mobil-delvac-city-logistics-m-5w-30.aspx" class="">Mobil Delvac&trade; City Logistics M 5W-30</a>, <a title="" target="" onclick="trackClick(this);" href="http://www.mobil.co.uk/UK-English-LCW/vanengineoils_mobil-delvac-city-logistics-v-5w-30.aspx" class="">Mobil Delvac&trade; City Logistics V 5W-30 </a>and <a title="" target="" onclick="trackClick(this);" href="http://www.mobil.co.uk/UK-English-LCW/vanengineoils_mobil-delvac-light-commercial-vehicle-e-10w-40.aspx" class="">Mobil Delvac&trade; Light Commercial Vehicle E 10W-40 </a>are formulated from high performance base oils and a superior balanced additive system to support optimum engine performance in recent diesel and gasoline engines as well as older models. With enhanced wear protection and increased thermal oxidation stability, this lubricant helps to prolong the life and maintain the efficiency of emission reduction systems such as the Mercedes Benz Diesel Particulate Filter (DPF).</p>

                        <p xmlns="">
                            <strong>How do I find the right oil for my Mercedes Benz van?</strong>
                        </p>

                        <p xmlns="">Using the right oil in light commercial vehicles is important to ensure you comply with Mercedes Benz specifications. Using the right Mobil Delvac product during routine servicing and according to your vehicle&rsquo;s manual will not affect the Mercedes Benz manufacturer&rsquo;s warranty. You can obtain a recommendation by using the 'Which oil' tool and searching by make and model.</p>
